# The root-level api/ directory is the Go service deployed to Cloud Run, NOT
# Vercel Serverless Functions. Without this, Vercel's zero-config detector
# picks up api/cmd/server/main.go and fails to build because it expects an
# exported Vercel Go handler.
#
# The leading slash is load-bearing: `api/` (unanchored) would also match
# `app/api/`, which is Next.js's Route Handler directory — excluding it
# silently 404s every /api/* route (including Auth.js callbacks).
/api/
